## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/prettystacktraceentry">PrettyStackTraceEntry</a> - This class is used to represent a frame of the &quot;pretty&quot; stack trace that is dumped when a program crashes.

You can define subclasses of this and declare them on the program stack: when they are constructed and destructed, they will add their symbolic frames to a virtual stack trace. This gets dumped out if the program crashes.

Definition at line 52 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/prettystacktrace-h">PrettyStackTrace.h</a>.
